Cape Town - Three MyCiTi buses collided in the Cape Town CBD on Tuesday morning bringing traffic to an abrupt halt around the scene of the crash. The collision occurred at the corners of Heerengracht and Hertzog Boulevard. ER24 paramedics, along with various other services, responded to the scene and treated 26 passengers who sustained minor to moderate injuries.  No serious or fatal injuries were reported. A Golden Arrow tow truck was dispatched to the scene to remove the damaged busses from the Civic Centre bus station. The cause of the accident is still unknown and is currently under investigation. Daily Voice